On December 3, 2020, the President signed several bills into law. These include H.R. 1773, which awards a Congressional Gold Medal to the women in the United States who joined the workforce during World War II, known as "Rosie the Riveter." Other bills include H.R. 1833, which designates a United States Postal Service facility in New York, and H.R. 3207, which designates a USPS facility in Pennsylvania. There are also bills that designate USPS facilities in Arkansas, California, Indiana, Brooklyn, North Carolina, Louisiana, and Charlotte. Lastly, S. 327, known as the "Wounded Veterans Recreation Act," authorizes the issuance of a lifetime National Parks and Federal Recreational Lands Pass without charge to veterans with service-connected disabilities.